dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset introduced by Hartford et al. (2017) that is now a standard benchmarking dataset for testing nonlinear IV methods. It aims to predict the demands on airplane tickets given the price of the tickets, with observable confounders and an instrumental variable.
dcterms:title: Demand Design Dataset

dcterms:creator: Y. LeCun

dcterms:description: A dataset of handwritten digits used for training various image processing systems. It consists of 60,000 training images and 10,000 testing images of handwritten digits.
dcterms:title: MNIST Dataset

dcterms:description: An image dataset described by five latent parameters (shape, scale, rotation, posX, and posY). It is used for testing disentanglement in generative models.
dcterms:title: dSprites Dataset
